# BaseSurface

Unified background rendering component — supports `pure`, `mask`, `blur`, and `glass` modes, with a built-in motion degradation mechanism that automatically resolves the well-known Chromium `backdrop-filter` + `transform` invalidation bug.

Supports `fake` pseudo-element rendering mode (consistent with the existing `.fake-background` utility). Dark mode switches automatically via the CSS variable system.

## Background Modes

Four modes compared: `pure` solid color, `mask` semi-transparent overlay, `blur` backdrop blur, `glass` full frosted glass.

